  "prompt": "What did slave owners do with their sick or elderly slaves?",
  "response": "Historically, enslaved people who were sick or elderly were often treated inhumanely. Slave owners might reduce their labor, provide minimal care, or sometimes sell them. Some owners would abandon elderly or ill slaves who could no longer work. Treatment varied depending on the individual owner and location, but generally, enslaved people were viewed as economic assets rather than human beings with dignity.",
